<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3529</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d564fn1">Sent via the Legation in China.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Omsk</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-24"><hi rend="italic">December 24,
                                        1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December
                                        26, 12.22 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>253. Situation Omsk to-day’s date. Small Bolshevik uprising in
                                village near Omsk (?) was supported [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] by
                                Czech and Cossack troops. Attempt on <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName>’s life in Chita with hand grenade. <pb facs="0554" n="464" xml:id="pg_464"/>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> not seriously
                                wounded. Czech National Council in Ekaterinburg has been disarmed
                                [dissolved?]. Situation Ufa front somewhat improved. Slight
                                Bolshevik unrest reported in Krasnoyarsk, otherwise quiet
                                Siberia.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_HEL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>